  </sponsors>
  <source>Seoul National University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  There is no definite tool for measurement of dehydration in children

        -  Subjective clinical dehydration scale is considered as valuable scoring system, but it
           cannot be reliable among clinicians sometimes.

        -  Some authors found Inferior vena cava/Aorta ratio can be a objective marker for
           dehydration

        -  However, there is no evidence of correlation between clinical dehydration scale and
           inferior vena cava/aorta ratio

        -  We will observe correlation between clinical dehydration scale and inferior vena
           cava/aorta ratio and change of the ratio according to hydration with intravenous normal
           saline infusion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
